SIMPLE: timorous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Timorous
<hw>Tim"or*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>timorosus</ets>, from L. <ets>timor</ets> fear; akin to
<ets>timere</ets> to fear. See <er>Timid</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Fearful of danger; timid; deficient in courage.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indicating, or caused by, fear; <as>as,
<ex>timorous</ex> doubts</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>timorous</xex>
apostasy of chuchmen.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Tim"or*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Tim"or*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Timorsome</ent>⟦br⟧
